pepper
salt
cayanne pepper
abode (spice, not sauce)

Dry rub a boston butt (pork shouler) and place in fridge in a ziplock bag. Let 30 coals whiten in a chimney, and place on one side of a standard coal bbq. Add soaked hickory woodchips (adding 8 coals per hour to the fire). Set meat in foil bed on the opposite side of grill and let grill for 3 hours covered. Let sit coverd in 275 degree oven for 3 more hours. Let stand covered for a final hour before pulling meat off bone and combining with sauce or brine.
